Albert Ernest Linton (February 17, 1880  August 6, 1957) was a Canadian amateur football (soccer) player who competed in the 1904 Summer Olympics. Linton was born in Scotland. In 1904 he was a member of the Galt F.C. team, which won the gold medal in the football tournament. He played both matches as a goalkeeper, keeping a clean slate in both. 
